# CloveJS multi-tenant MCP example — HTTP requests
#
# Read natively by JetBrains IDEs (Run > HTTP Client) and VS Code's "REST
# Client" extension (humao.rest-client). Click "Send Request" above a block, or
# run them top to bottom — later blocks reuse tokens captured from earlier ones.
#
# Start the server first: npm run dev -w clovejs-example-multi-tenant-mcp
#
# The MCP protocol handshake (initialize -> tool calls, with an Mcp-Session-Id
# and Server-Sent-Events responses) is best driven by a real MCP client. These
# requests cover the OAuth half: discovery, rejection, and getting a token. See
# the README for the client side.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Unauthenticated MCP call — refused with a WWW-Authenticate challenge (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1, "method": "initialize",
  "params": { "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18", "capabilities": {},
              "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "1.0" } } }

### Protected-resource metadata (RFC 9728) — where to get a token
GET {{baseUrl}}/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource/mcp

### The dev authorization server's public JWKS
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/dev/jwks

### Mint an acme token (read + write by default)
# @name acmeToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dev/token
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tenant": "acme" }

### Mint a read-only globex token
# @name globexToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dev/token
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tenant": "globex", "scopes": ["notes:read"] }

### Authenticated initialize as acme — accepted (200, Server-Sent-Events)
# The response carries an Mcp-Session-Id header; a real client uses it for
# follow-up tool calls on the same connection.
POST {{baseUrl}}/mcp
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json, text/event-stream
Authorization: Bearer {{acmeToken.response.body.access_token}}

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1, "method": "initialize",
  "params": { "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18", "capabilities": {},
              "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "1.0" } } }

### An unknown tenant is rejected by the dev authorization server (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/dev/token
Content-Type: application/json

{ "tenant": "unknown" }
